does anyone have nerve pain from surgery i had surgery behind my ear in my ear twice in my life and i have some pain when i push on that spot on my head it hurts should i tell my surgeon that absolutely you could have any number of complications from the surgery or you could have something new that is related to the surgery the fact that you have a desire to push on the spot indicates something is not right a common complication from surgery is an accumulation of blood at the surgical site and that can be dangerous talk to your doctor's nurse first and she'll give you some priority on getting a new appointment Surgery Medicine Plastic surgery Orthopedic surgery Traumatic brain injury Stomach cancer Penis Hip fracture Carpal tunnel syndrome Intersex surgery Urinary incontinence Prostate cancer Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Triage William Stewart Halsted Neurosurgery Female genital cutting Scrubs Local anesthesia Colorectal cancer Endometriosis Endoscopic thoracic sympathectomy Acoustic neuroma Cancer Stroke Cryptorchidism Syringomyelia Cholecystectomy Anesthesia Diabetic retinopathy Pneumonia Glossary of medical terms related to communications disorders Transsexuality Sex reassignment surgery Bone fracture Tourniquet Acromegaly Earring Reflex sympathetic dystrophy syndrome Inguinal hernia Dialysis History of anatomy in the 17th and 18th centuries Suture Oral and maxillofacial surgery Cardiac surgery Crohn's disease Migraine Chronic fatigue syndrome Insulin Hernia Vomiting Breastfeeding Nurse Spina bifida Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Lethal injection Castration Retinal detachment Minimally invasive Fecal incontinence Gout Prolactinoma Surgical instruments Radiosurgery Acne Trigeminal neuralgia History of intersex surgery Physician Radiation therapy Psychic surgery Jayant Patel Replacement joint Penis enlargement Renal cell carcinoma Mastoiditis Cephalic disorder Lung cancer Acupuncture Balance disorder Intraocular lens Gastroesophageal reflux disease Epilepsy Veterina